include / nitf

FileHeader.h File Reference

Detailed Description

Contains the API for objects in a NITF file header.

This file contains the declarations for all of the objects which are loaded or saved during file read/write operations.

Definition in file FileHeader.h.

#include "nitf/System.h"

nitf_FileHeader* nitf_FileHeader_construct (  nitf_Error *  error  ) 
 

We want to construct and init the whole object. We NULL-initialize all sub-objects before creating them, so that, in the event of an exception, memory deallocation is easier. This is tedious, but prevents bug-prone problems

Parameters:
error An error to populate on a NULL return
Returns:
The newly allocated file header, or NULL upon failure

void nitf_FileHeader_destruct (  nitf_FileHeader **  fh  ) 
 

Destruct all sub-objects, and make sure that we kill this object too.

Parameters:
fh The file header to destroy. We point fh at NULL.
